HB 928 Original 2026 Regular Session Fontenot
Abstract: Provides for applicability of the Louisiana State Uniform Construction Code and
compliance review by the fire marshal.
Proposed law, if enacted, supercedes certain provisions of Act No. 534 of the 2024 Regular
Session of the Legislature to the extent that those provisions conflict with proposed law.
Present law provides structures and movables shall comply with the Life Safety Code of the
National Fire Protection Association.
Proposed law provides the fire marshal shall review every structure or movable for
compliance with the Louisiana Uniform Construction Code and conduct preliminary review
